<DOC><DOCNO> AP891204-0183 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-12-04-89 2243EST</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-BRF-CanadaTrain     12-04 0126</FIRST><SECOND>AM-BRF-Canada Train,0129</SECOND><HEAD>Truck Hits Freight Train, Driver Killed</HEAD><DATELINE>HOWICK, Quebec (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   An oil truck crashed into a moving freighttrain Monday, killing the truck driver and derailing 15 freightcars, police and witnesses reported.   The accident occurred at a crossing 36 miles south of Montrealat 1 p.m. Two households were evacuated because of fumes from thehour-long fire, according to police.   ``The sun was really bright and he (the trucker) may not haveseen the lights flashing at the level crossing,'' said SteveTucker, who works at a store.   ``I heard the train whistle blowing, but I don't think the truckdriver heard it in time. I was the second one down to the crossingand there was nothing we could do.''</TEXT></DOC>